com.interpss.core.aclf
Interface AclfBus

All Superinterfaces:
Bus, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ExtensionElement, IAclfBus, IAclfBusAdaptation, IAclfBusAdjustment, IAclfBusFunc, IAdaptable, IBusSwitchBreakModel, NameTag, NetworkedElement, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
All Known Subinterfaces:
AclfBusChildNetRef, AcscBus
All Known Implementing Classes:
AclfBusChildNetRefImpl, AclfBusImpl, AcscBusImpl
public interface AclfBus
extends Bus, IAclfBus, IAclfBusFunc, IAclfBusAdaptation, IAclfBusAdjustment

A representation of the model object 'Bus'. AclfBus class is for storing bus information for AC loadflow analysis. AclfBus could be extended using IAclfBus or ICustomLoad interface.

The following features are supported:

  • Gen Code
  • Gen Code Base Case
  • Load Code
  • Voltage Mag
  • Voltage Ang
  • Gen P
  • Gen Q
  • Load P
  • Load Q
  • Shunt Y
  • Exp Load P
  • Exp Load Q
  • Load Dist Factor
  • Gen Part Factor
  • QGen Limit
  • PGen Limit
  • VLimit
  • Dclf Inject P
  • Function Load
  • Bus Control

See Also:
AclfPackage.getAclfBus()

b11ii

double b11ii()
Calculate bus B11ii, in pu.
1) phase shifter not represented;
2) 'I', 'Z' load not represented
3) shunt Y not represented

b1ii

double b1ii()
Calculate bus B1ii, in pu
1) shunt susceptance not represented
2) off-nominal taps not represented
3) 'I', 'Z' load not represented
4) grounded branch not represented
5) shunt Y not represented

getLossPFactor

double getLossPFactor(NetPathWalkDirectionEnum direction,
                      double totalLossPU)
Loss participation factor of this bus. For source->sink walk direction, the bus is treated as a Load bus, for source<-sink walk direction, the bus is treated as a gen bus.
